WEBVTT

00:00:00.960 --> 00:00:02.500
Okay, you guys.

00:00:02.520 --> 00:00:03.140
Thanks, Tori.

00:00:03.140 --> 00:00:04.340
Yeah, thank you.

00:00:04.340 --> 00:00:06.020
Sorry for being late.

00:00:06.140 --> 00:00:07.180
Thanks for waiting for me.

00:00:07.320 --> 00:00:08.060
Hi, everyone.

00:00:08.060 --> 00:00:08.900
I'm Tori.

00:00:08.900 --> 00:00:10.020
Welcome to my talk.

00:00:10.020 --> 00:00:13.500
It used to be what 350,000 users taught me,

00:00:13.500 --> 00:00:16.210
but hell yeah.

00:00:16.220 --> 00:00:18.380
Now it's 400,000.

00:00:18.380 --> 00:00:19.220
Holy crap.

00:00:19.220 --> 00:00:21.940
What I'm hoping to do today, and I'm hoping

00:00:21.940 --> 00:00:24.900
it's going to be useful, is just distill some of

00:00:24.900 --> 00:00:27.770
my learnings and reads Nye's learnings from this

00:00:27.770 --> 00:00:31.200
past year and package them up here for you today with the

00:00:31.250 --> 00:00:34.920
hopes that you don't make the same mistakes that we made

00:00:35.030 --> 00:00:35.180
.

00:00:35.180 --> 00:00:40.610
And oh, how do I get over there?

00:00:40.620 --> 00:00:45.240
Oh, there we are.

00:00:45.240 --> 00:00:46.500
Wait, sorry, you guys.

00:00:46.500 --> 00:00:47.120
Hold on a second.

00:00:47.120 --> 00:00:50.360
My mouse is, there she is.

00:00:50.460 --> 00:00:51.860
Was I over there?

00:00:51.880 --> 00:00:53.350
Yeah, and that's on me.

00:00:55.220 --> 00:00:58.800
But also with the caveat that we could be completely wrong about

00:00:58.930 --> 00:01:01.300
the things that we're suggesting, so do what's right

00:01:01.420 --> 00:01:01.940
for you, okay?

00:01:01.940 --> 00:01:05.180
So this is the Skylight Squad.

00:01:05.240 --> 00:01:08.430
This is Reed and I, and we built Skylight Social

00:01:08.470 --> 00:01:08.760
.

00:01:08.760 --> 00:01:11.840
Skylight is a video Instagram-y style app on the

00:01:11.840 --> 00:01:12.800
protocol.

00:01:13.600 --> 00:01:17.780
We started building last year in January 2025, right before the

00:01:17.780 --> 00:01:18.880
big TikTok ban.

00:01:18.880 --> 00:01:21.830
We launched in April and, like I said, have since

00:01:21.830 --> 00:01:26.090
grown to over 400,000 organic downloads, no paid ads

00:01:26.090 --> 00:01:26.890
, insane.

00:01:26.940 --> 00:01:31.210
And that's Skylight right there on your guys' right

00:01:31.210 --> 00:01:31.540
.

00:01:31.540 --> 00:01:32.320
Oh, she's beautiful.

00:01:34.640 --> 00:01:36.560
Oh, and there's transitions on this.

00:01:36.560 --> 00:01:37.500
Woo, okay.

00:01:37.500 --> 00:01:40.740
So with the help of my co-founder, Reed,

00:01:40.880 --> 00:01:44.940
I've kind of distilled my learnings into these three

00:01:44.940 --> 00:01:48.130
main pillars, which hopefully will help organize this thing.

00:01:48.160 --> 00:01:49.540
Prove yourself wrong.

00:01:49.540 --> 00:01:51.920
We win together and share your story.

00:01:51.920 --> 00:01:54.860
So prove yourself wrong.

00:01:54.860 --> 00:01:56.790
Right now, a lot of you are builders, so you

00:01:56.790 --> 00:01:59.460
probably, like we did, have a hypothesis of what you

00:01:59.460 --> 00:02:00.450
think users want.

00:02:00.880 --> 00:02:03.820
And your new North Star is to try and test whether that

00:02:03.820 --> 00:02:05.230
hypothesis is right.

00:02:05.240 --> 00:02:08.480
Not to build every feature, not to fix every bug.

00:02:08.480 --> 00:02:11.350
God knows we still have bugs in Skylight, but get

00:02:11.350 --> 00:02:14.830
as quickly as possible to the answer to this question, I

00:02:14.830 --> 00:02:15.300
think.

00:02:15.300 --> 00:02:17.730
Hot tip.

00:02:17.840 --> 00:02:20.480
The first thing you build is almost certainly the wrong thing.

00:02:20.480 --> 00:02:22.740
This doesn't mean your insight was wrong.

00:02:22.740 --> 00:02:25.510
This just means that maybe the solution that you built, users

00:02:25.510 --> 00:02:26.980
don't actually want to use it.

00:02:27.100 --> 00:02:30.580
Our first version of Skylight, over 10,000 people

00:02:30.580 --> 00:02:32.440
entered, and all of them left.

00:02:32.440 --> 00:02:33.970
Not ideal.

00:02:33.980 --> 00:02:35.090
I don't recommend.

00:02:35.140 --> 00:02:37.140
Makes you sad on the inside.

00:02:37.140 --> 00:02:40.320
In fact, we've made at least three versions of Sky

00:02:40.320 --> 00:02:41.850
light's interface.

00:02:41.860 --> 00:02:45.360
We even dabbled in a horizontal swiping interface.

00:02:45.360 --> 00:02:49.420
Again, spoiler alert, that absolutely did not work.

00:02:49.660 --> 00:02:51.130
And people literally hated it.

00:02:51.180 --> 00:02:53.980
The comment you see here, yeah, there was a lot

00:02:53.980 --> 00:02:54.660
of them.

00:02:54.660 --> 00:02:57.720
People on the internet are sometimes mean.

00:02:57.720 --> 00:03:00.150
Be nice to me in my comments, you guys, okay

00:03:00.310 --> 00:03:00.440
?

00:03:00.440 --> 00:03:04.020
But don't crash out if your first version doesn't work

00:03:04.150 --> 00:03:04.420
.

00:03:04.420 --> 00:03:07.420
I think we all have a couple of shots at bat.

00:03:07.420 --> 00:03:09.910
The first couple people who see this, you know there's

00:03:10.010 --> 00:03:12.930
7 billion, wait, maybe 8 billion people in the world

00:03:13.030 --> 00:03:15.640
, you have some opportunity to try again.

00:03:15.660 --> 00:03:19.140
And ironically, our best version of Skylight wasn't the

00:03:19.140 --> 00:03:20.760
one that users asked for.

00:03:20.860 --> 00:03:24.050
And on social, it often isn't.

00:03:24.080 --> 00:03:26.970
So see what they say with their feet and with their,

00:03:26.970 --> 00:03:29.460
you know, the time they spend on your platform.

00:03:30.820 --> 00:03:33.660
And to that end, I highly recommend PostHog for

00:03:33.680 --> 00:03:34.570
Analytics.

00:03:34.600 --> 00:03:36.320
This really saved us.

00:03:36.320 --> 00:03:39.440
Again, people will tell you with their actions whether or not

00:03:39.440 --> 00:03:41.290
they're enjoying what you build.

00:03:41.300 --> 00:03:44.750
Warning, don't use Analytics to convince yourself it's working

00:03:44.750 --> 00:03:44.880
.

00:03:45.000 --> 00:03:47.350
You're not trying to get retention from 3.

00:03:47.350 --> 00:03:48.070
2% to 3.

00:03:48.070 --> 00:03:50.160
4%, especially in the beginning.

00:03:50.160 --> 00:03:53.740
Yeah, try not to chase these numbers.

00:03:53.760 --> 00:03:55.040
Just use it as a gut check.

00:03:55.040 --> 00:03:56.920
Our user is liking what you made.

00:03:56.920 --> 00:03:58.590
This was really helpful for us.

00:03:58.900 --> 00:04:01.560
They have a, PostHog has a free startup program

00:04:01.560 --> 00:04:01.810
.

00:04:01.820 --> 00:04:03.670
I know some, a lot of people here, when I

00:04:03.690 --> 00:04:05.900
've told them about this, they're like, oh,

00:04:05.990 --> 00:04:07.140
I built my own analytics.

00:04:07.140 --> 00:04:08.610
And I'm like, wow, you're a badass.

00:04:08.700 --> 00:04:13.070
But yeah, we really were thankful for that when we got

00:04:13.070 --> 00:04:14.940
hit with a fat bill.

00:04:14.940 --> 00:04:17.610
Woke up freaking out and then got an email like,

00:04:17.610 --> 00:04:20.490
hey, you should really join the startup program.

00:04:20.500 --> 00:04:22.800
We're like, oh, wait, that would be really

00:04:22.800 --> 00:04:23.340
great.

00:04:23.360 --> 00:04:25.300
Yeah.

00:04:25.300 --> 00:04:26.770
Okay.

00:04:27.760 --> 00:04:30.180
Pillar number two, we are in this together.

00:04:30.180 --> 00:04:32.620
The people in this room, the people at this conference,

00:04:32.770 --> 00:04:34.640
they are going to be your greatest strength.

00:04:34.640 --> 00:04:36.030
I know that they were ours.

00:04:36.080 --> 00:04:40.080
And I truly believe that our communal collaboration is going to make

00:04:40.080 --> 00:04:41.880
or break the things that we build.

00:04:41.880 --> 00:04:46.100
Hot shout out to these five folks.

00:04:46.100 --> 00:04:48.380
And gosh, honestly, a ton of people.

00:04:48.380 --> 00:04:50.820
They have talked me off the ledge.

00:04:50.900 --> 00:04:54.090
They have physically come into my code base and written things.

00:04:55.100 --> 00:04:56.780
We have collaborated with them.

00:04:56.780 --> 00:04:59.290
Some of the things that they have built now exist inside of

00:04:59.370 --> 00:05:00.820
Skylight, making it better.

00:05:00.820 --> 00:05:01.820
Yeah.

00:05:01.820 --> 00:05:04.540
Black Sky, Graze, Stream Place, Germ.

00:05:04.540 --> 00:05:06.720
I just can't thank these guys enough.

00:05:06.740 --> 00:05:07.580
And that's Jimmy.

00:05:07.580 --> 00:05:08.980
He lets us use his space.

00:05:09.000 --> 00:05:09.940
Yeah.

00:05:10.440 --> 00:05:12.440
So talk with the people here.

00:05:12.440 --> 00:05:15.260
Try and get a group together so that when you're inevitably

00:05:15.280 --> 00:05:17.730
crashing out in the middle of the night, you have someone

00:05:17.730 --> 00:05:18.130
to call.

00:05:21.160 --> 00:05:22.630
This is a big one for us.

00:05:22.640 --> 00:05:24.520
The app protocol is a resource.

00:05:24.520 --> 00:05:26.640
I highly recommend using it.

00:05:26.640 --> 00:05:29.830
The way that we chose to use it was to utilize Blue

00:05:30.010 --> 00:05:32.830
Sky's lexicon so that a Skylight post is

00:05:32.830 --> 00:05:34.420
the same as a Blue Sky post.

00:05:34.420 --> 00:05:37.330
And this was very intentional on our part because we wanted people

00:05:37.330 --> 00:05:40.780
who stepped into Skylight to not have that feeling of emptiness

00:05:40.990 --> 00:05:42.240
in a social network.

00:05:42.700 --> 00:05:45.510
And I'm not saying that this is right for everyone to

00:05:45.560 --> 00:05:45.940
do.

00:05:45.960 --> 00:05:48.580
I'm just saying that there are some ways that we can

00:05:48.580 --> 00:05:51.160
leverage distribution, the tools that exist.

00:05:52.220 --> 00:05:53.320
And I think you should.

00:05:53.320 --> 00:05:54.660
That's why it exists.

00:05:54.660 --> 00:05:57.420
That's what kind of makes us better than all those other

00:05:57.420 --> 00:05:58.480
sucky platforms.

00:05:58.480 --> 00:06:00.800
Use it if you can.

00:06:00.800 --> 00:06:05.170
And if you, what is it called?

00:06:05.200 --> 00:06:07.600
If you want to brainstorm on how you might be able to

00:06:07.600 --> 00:06:11.070
leverage what exists in the protocol to make it easier to market

00:06:11.190 --> 00:06:13.910
your thing, I honestly wouldn't even, I mean,

00:06:13.960 --> 00:06:16.180
you can come talk to me, but I would highly recommend

00:06:16.290 --> 00:06:17.640
talking to my co-founder, Reed.

00:06:17.640 --> 00:06:19.920
I swear this is like his bread and butter.

00:06:19.920 --> 00:06:23.110
He's really good at thinking about how you can get your

00:06:23.150 --> 00:06:26.850
idea in front of more faces or like utilize what exists for

00:06:27.030 --> 00:06:28.900
people to see what you're building.

00:06:28.900 --> 00:06:34.950
Most folks won't get it first that we are actively working

00:06:35.040 --> 00:06:36.440
together.

00:06:36.440 --> 00:06:39.900
This is something I constantly have to explain to people.

00:06:39.900 --> 00:06:43.700
I had an advisor emailing me, kind of freaking out

00:06:43.710 --> 00:06:44.010
.

00:06:44.040 --> 00:06:46.470
They're like, what are you going to do about divine

00:06:46.630 --> 00:06:46.760
?

00:06:46.760 --> 00:06:48.900
And I remember I was like laughing.

00:06:48.900 --> 00:06:50.820
I was like, cheer them on.

00:06:50.820 --> 00:06:53.260
That's so cool what Rabble is doing.

00:06:53.300 --> 00:06:56.430
I'm so freaking excited that we now, all of us

00:06:56.430 --> 00:06:59.040
have access to Vine's old videos.

00:06:59.040 --> 00:07:02.270
I mean, I had to remind my advisor, this is

00:07:02.270 --> 00:07:03.410
open social.

00:07:03.480 --> 00:07:05.500
This is the whole point of what we're doing.

00:07:05.500 --> 00:07:09.080
I on Skylight now have direct access to showcasing Vine

00:07:09.190 --> 00:07:10.160
's videos.

00:07:10.880 --> 00:07:13.990
And it's not just because, you know, Divine exists

00:07:13.990 --> 00:07:14.280
.

00:07:14.280 --> 00:07:17.790
Like Rabble legitimately built a tool to make it easier for

00:07:17.790 --> 00:07:19.540
us to port over those videos.

00:07:19.540 --> 00:07:21.220
And that's what open social is all about.

00:07:21.320 --> 00:07:22.780
Yeah.

00:07:22.780 --> 00:07:27.710
So I really, really hope, you know, he gets

00:07:27.830 --> 00:07:30.800
out there and he kills it.

00:07:30.800 --> 00:07:31.700
And he already is.

00:07:31.820 --> 00:07:34.510
And I hope that for everyone who's building on this protocol

00:07:34.510 --> 00:07:37.840
, because we have really big fish to fry.

00:07:37.840 --> 00:07:40.660
And it's almost certainly not each other.

00:07:40.660 --> 00:07:43.060
There are a ton of badasses in this space.

00:07:43.060 --> 00:07:46.100
Find them, collaborate with them, cheer them on.

00:07:46.100 --> 00:07:49.090
Because if they take down the monster in the room, then

00:07:49.090 --> 00:07:50.670
we all get to win, right?

00:07:51.080 --> 00:07:51.360
Okay.

00:07:51.360 --> 00:07:53.020
And that's his real yacht, by the way.

00:07:53.020 --> 00:07:54.900
Shout out to Marky Mark.

00:07:54.900 --> 00:07:56.940
Okay.

00:07:56.940 --> 00:08:00.740
Tell your story.

00:08:00.740 --> 00:08:03.620
Marketing is absolutely a part of what you're building.

00:08:03.620 --> 00:08:06.350
Storytelling is a part of what you will have to

00:08:06.350 --> 00:08:06.780
do.

00:08:06.780 --> 00:08:08.680
We want folks using these things.

00:08:08.680 --> 00:08:11.630
So we have to make sure we build community around them.

00:08:11.640 --> 00:08:14.080
And I know you guys know that.

00:08:14.220 --> 00:08:17.460
Building in public really worked well for us.

00:08:17.500 --> 00:08:19.860
If you're up for it, obviously can't recommend short

00:08:19.860 --> 00:08:20.740
form video more.

00:08:21.340 --> 00:08:22.680
Make sure to post it on Skylight.

00:08:22.680 --> 00:08:26.480
We made a video before we ever wrote a line of code

00:08:26.490 --> 00:08:26.790
.

00:08:26.820 --> 00:08:30.210
And maybe your medium isn't video, but highly recommend trying

00:08:30.210 --> 00:08:31.190
to figure it out.

00:08:31.280 --> 00:08:34.150
And to that point, if you find a format that works

00:08:34.150 --> 00:08:37.200
, then roll that thing until the cows come home.

00:08:37.200 --> 00:08:38.440
You see this video?

00:08:38.440 --> 00:08:41.620
I have made this style of video where I point at these

00:08:41.620 --> 00:08:43.580
guys who suck so many times.

00:08:43.580 --> 00:08:46.190
I've gotten over a million views with this style of video

00:08:46.200 --> 00:08:46.420
.

00:08:46.440 --> 00:08:49.680
It took me a lot of different tries to find this format

00:08:49.740 --> 00:08:50.020
.

00:08:50.520 --> 00:08:52.960
But if you try something that works, stick to it.

00:08:52.980 --> 00:08:57.350
And yes, we have to show up where people are.

00:08:57.480 --> 00:08:59.150
Yes, I am on these platforms.

00:08:59.280 --> 00:09:01.680
And yes, I am telling the people on these platforms about

00:09:01.680 --> 00:09:03.650
OpenSocial and telling them to get over here.

00:09:03.720 --> 00:09:05.400
And please join me.

00:09:05.420 --> 00:09:07.680
Don't leave me alone.

00:09:07.780 --> 00:09:09.830
I want to be able to tag the things that you built

00:09:09.830 --> 00:09:12.770
on these platforms when I inevitably make a video about them.

00:09:12.820 --> 00:09:13.180
Okay?

00:09:13.740 --> 00:09:15.210
So join me over here.

00:09:15.280 --> 00:09:17.720
I know that's shocking to say at an OpenSocial

00:09:17.870 --> 00:09:18.800
conference.

00:09:18.800 --> 00:09:21.410
But some language that helped us.

00:09:21.420 --> 00:09:22.780
Decentralized, never work.

00:09:22.780 --> 00:09:25.200
Never say the word app protocol, unfortunately.

00:09:25.200 --> 00:09:27.620
OpenSocial.

00:09:27.620 --> 00:09:29.520
Emphasizing creator ownership.

00:09:29.520 --> 00:09:30.320
That did work.

00:09:32.020 --> 00:09:34.800
Please put your app logo on the internet.

00:09:34.800 --> 00:09:36.980
So when I make a video about you, I know I

00:09:36.990 --> 00:09:38.840
can have access to your logo.

00:09:38.840 --> 00:09:41.280
Not just on your blue sky page.

00:09:41.360 --> 00:09:41.700
Okay?

00:09:41.700 --> 00:09:43.240
Because it's really hard to screenshot those.

00:09:43.260 --> 00:09:46.080
That's a personal request by me.

00:09:46.100 --> 00:09:47.760
Okay.

00:09:47.760 --> 00:09:48.560
That's it.

00:09:48.560 --> 00:09:49.760
Thanks, you guys.

00:09:49.760 --> 00:09:50.520
Woo!

00:09:50.530 --> 00:09:53.580
Woo!
